REM Comprehensive test for HOLD/RELEASE and MEDIA/GLOBE commands
REM This script demonstrates all new features added to WiFiDuck

DEFAULTDELAY 200

REM ======================
REM HOLD and RELEASE Tests
REM ======================

REM Test 1: Hold SHIFT to type uppercase
REM Expected: Types "HELLO WORLD"
HOLD SHIFT
STRING hello world
RELEASE

REM Test 2: Multiple modifiers
REM Expected: Ctrl+Shift+T (Reopen closed tab in browser)
HOLD CTRL
HOLD SHIFT
STRING t
RELEASE

REM Test 3: Complex key combination
REM Expected: Ctrl+Alt+Delete on Windows
HOLD CTRL
HOLD ALT
DELETE
RELEASE

REM ======================
REM MEDIA Command Tests
REM ======================

REM Test 4: Volume controls
MEDIA VOLUMEUP
DELAY 300
MEDIA VOLUMEUP
DELAY 300
MEDIA VOLUMEDOWN
DELAY 300
MEDIA MUTE

REM Test 5: Media playback
MEDIA PLAYPAUSE
DELAY 2000
MEDIA NEXT
DELAY 1000
MEDIA STOP

REM Test 6: Browser controls
MEDIA BROWSER
DELAY 1000
MEDIA REFRESH
DELAY 500
MEDIA BACK

REM Test 7: System controls
MEDIA CALC
DELAY 1000
MEDIA EMAIL
DELAY 1000
MEDIA MYCOMPUTER

REM ======================
REM GLOBE Key Test
REM ======================

REM Test 8: Globe key
GLOBE
DELAY 500

REM ======================
REM Combined Tests
REM ======================

REM Test 9: HOLD with STRING
REM Types a URL in the address bar with proper formatting
HOLD CTRL
STRING l
RELEASE
DELAY 200
STRING https://github.com/rkturbo/WiFiDuck
ENTER

REM Test 10: Multiple HOLD/RELEASE cycles
HOLD SHIFT
STRING test1
RELEASE
STRING normaltext
HOLD SHIFT
STRING test2
RELEASE

REM End of test script
